elements.description:
The datetime components rely on [Moment.js](https://momentjs.com/) and [Moment Timezone](https://momentjs.com/timezone/).

### Usage

    <px-datetime-range-field from-moment="{{...}}" to-moment="{{...}}">
    </px-datetime-range-field>


### Styling

The following custom properties are available for styling. Please also refer to px-forms-design for additional style variables used by this component.

Custom property | Description
:----------------|:-------------
`--px-datetime-range-field-to-color` | Text color of the "TO" between start and end date input fields
`--px-datetime-range-field-margin-between-fields` | When `showFieldTitles` is true this is the amount of space between the fields

properties.name: keyEventTarget
properties.description:
The EventTarget that will be firing relevant KeyboardEvents. Set it to
`null` to disable the listeners.

properties.name: stopKeyboardEventPropagation
properties.description:
If true, this property will cause the implementing element to
automatically stop propagation on any handled KeyboardEvents.

properties.name: _imperativeKeyBindings
properties.description: own properties of everything on the "prototype".

properties.name: keyBindings
properties.description: Key bindings for iron-a11y-keys-behavior

properties.name: blockFutureDates
properties.description: Set this attribute when you do not want to allow future dates to be selected (future dates will be disabled and unclickable).

properties.name: blockPastDates
properties.description: Set this attribute when you do not want to allow past dates to be selected (past dates will be disabled and unclickable).

properties.name: __localizationCache
properties.description:
Internal singleton cache. This is the private implementation of the
behaviour; don't interact with it directly.

properties.name: language
properties.description: set a default for localizing

properties.name: resources
properties.description: List of key/values to be included for translating this component
properties.defaultValue: {"en":{"from can not be later than to":"from can not be later than to","from":"from","TO":"TO"}}

properties.name: formats
useKeyIfMissing
properties.description:
Use the key for localization if value for  language is missing. Should
always be true for px components

properties.name: localize
properties.description:
Translates a string to the current `language`. Any parameters to the
string should be passed in order, as follows:
`localize(stringKey, param1Name, param1Value, param2Name, param2Value)`

properties.name: bubbleEvent
properties.description: If true, will bubble up the event to the parents

properties.name: timeZone
properties.description:
Moment-timezone string for using a specific timezone. See
http://momentjs.com/timezone/docs/#/data-loading/getting-zone-names/.

If not provided, tries to guess the current local timezone.

properties.name: minDate
properties.description: The minimum / earliest allowed date, as a a Moment object or an ISO 8601 String (dates before this will be disabled and unclickable).

properties.name: maxDate
properties.description: The maximum / latest allowed date, as a a Moment object or an ISO 8601 String (dates after this will be disabled and unclickable).

properties.name: fromMoment
properties.description: Moment object start date & time

properties.name: toMoment
properties.description: Moment object end date & time

properties.name: presetRanges
_tempFromMomentObj
properties.description:
Temporary from moment object used for validation and displaying.
This object should be used by subcomponents when we want to "try"
a value and see the result of validation AND/OR give us the ability
to rollback (cancel) or apply

properties.name: _tempToMomentObj
properties.description:
Temporary to moment object used for validation and displaying.
This object should be used by subcomponents when we want to "try"
a value and see the result of validation AND/OR give us the ability
to rollback (cancel) or apply

properties.name: showButtons
properties.description: Whether to show Apply and Cancel buttons in the components

properties.name: isValid
properties.description: Boolean stating if the date, time, and range are valid.

properties.name: validationErrorMessage
properties.description: String used to describe the current invalid state

properties.name: dateFormat
properties.description:
Moment format string for the DATE format to display/validate this field against
(see http://momentjs.com/docs/#/parsing/string-format/)

properties.name: timeFormat
properties.description:
Moment format string for the TIME format to display/validate this field against
(see http://momentjs.com/docs/#/parsing/string-format/)

properties.name: showTimeZone
properties.description:
Can be set to show the timezone. Can have 4 possible values:
 - 'dropdown': Shows the time zone as a dropdown which the user can use to select a different time zone. Only contains a subset of all time zones.
 - 'extendedDropdown': Shows the time zone as a dropdown which the user can use to select a different time zone. Contains all existing time zones (588) from the IANA tz database.
 - 'text': Shows the time zone as non-editable text.
 - 'abbreviatedText': Shows the abbreviated time zone as non editable text (such as PST, EST, etc). Note: many time zones do not have an abbreviation.

properties.name: hideTime
properties.description: Controls whether time should be hidden in the fields.

properties.name: hideDate
properties.description: Controls whether date should be hidden in the fields.

properties.name: hideIcon
properties.description: Controls whether the calendar/clock icons should be hidden.

properties.name: required
properties.description:
Boolean stating if the range field is required.
Will result in an error if left blank.

properties.name: _isRangeValid
properties.description: Used internally to determine if the range validation error should be displayed.

properties.name: _fromValid
properties.description: Reflects if the 'from' field is valid

properties.name: _toValid
properties.description: Reflects if the 'to' field is valid

properties.name: _showFromValidationMessage
properties.description: Used to determine which validation message to show when there are multiple invalid fields.

properties.name: _showToValidationMessage
properties.description: Used to determine which validation message to show when there are multiple invalid fields.

properties.name: hideValidationMessages
properties.description: Hide all validation messages

properties.name: allowWrap
properties.description:
Allows the component to wrap the fields and buttons when
the horizontal space can't fit them all on one line.

Fields will automatically wrap if `fullWidth` is set to true.

properties.name: fullWidth
properties.description:
For layout purposes.
This will display grid the fields. `showFieldTitles` must be true for styles to take effect.

`--px-datetime-range-field-column-min-width` (default: 250px) - controls
the min-width that each field is allowed to be before the grid wraps.

`--px-datetime-range-field-margin-between-fields` (default: 10px) - controls
the horizontal spacing between the fields.

This means each field will take up half of the container that `px-datetime-range-field`
is in, minus the space between the fields. When the container scales smaller than 510px or
`(--px-datetime-range-field-column-min-width * 2 + --px-datetime-range-field-margin-between-fields)`.

The fields will wrap under each other regardless of the `allow-wrap` prop in every browser except for IE.
Setting this property will override anything set in the `--px-datetime-range-field-justify-fields`

properties.name: showFieldTitles
properties.description:
This will remove the `to` in-between the fields and
add titles above the fields. This allows for a
more flexible design.

methods.name: addOwnKeyBinding
methods.description:
Can be used to imperatively add a key binding to the implementing
element. This is the imperative equivalent of declaring a keybinding
in the `keyBindings` prototype property.

methods.name: removeOwnKeyBindings
methods.description: When called, will remove all imperatively-added key bindings.

methods.name: keyboardEventMatchesKeys
methods.description: Returns true if a keyboard event matches `eventString`.

methods.name: __computeLocalize
methods.description: Returns a computed `localize` method, based on the current `language`.

methods.name: _preserveTime
methods.description:
Copies the time in toPreserve to dest and returns dest.
used in `px-calendar-picker`, `px-datetime-picker`, and `px-datetime-range-panel`

methods.name: _localeChanged
methods.description: make sure the moment obj picks up the possibly new moment locale

methods.name: _timeZoneChanged
methods.description: makes sure the moment objects reflect the timezone

methods.name: _validateRangeOrder
methods.description: Validation for the range. Makes sure the ranges are in chronological order

return.desc: true if chronological order, false otherwise

methods.name: _applyTempRangeMoment
methods.description: Applies value of temp moment to public momentObj

methods.name: _rollbackTempFromMoment
methods.description: Rollback value of temp fromMoment to use public momentObj

methods.name: _rollbackTempToMoment
methods.description: Rollback value of temp toMoment to use public momentObj

methods.name: _localeChangedTemp
methods.description: make sure the moment obj pick up the possibly new moment locale

methods.name: _timeZoneChangedTemp
methods.description: makes sure the moment objects reflect the timezone

methods.name: _validateInput
methods.description: Validation function for 'px-datetime-entry'

methods.name: _validateField
methods.description:
Validate a complete field
called in px-datetime-field and px-datetime-range-field

params.name: funcOrigin
params.description: The function that called validation. Used for `_handleIncompleteEntries`

return.desc:
validation result:
- MomentObj - The validated new moment obj
- False - If the new moment is invalid
- FieldSame - If the new moment is the same as the old moment
- FieldBlank - If the visible field(s) are blank

methods.name: _validateMomentObj
methods.description:
Validate a moment object
called in from _validateField and px-datetime-field

return.desc:
validation result:
- MomentObj - The validated new moment obj
- False - If the new moment is invalid
- FieldSame - If the new moment is the same as the old moment

methods.name: _validField
methods.description: Reset field to valid

methods.name: _invalidField
methods.description:
Set field to invalid
Set validation Error Message, turn on validation error, set isValid to false, and fire event.

methods.name: _entryInputString
methods.description: loop through array of the entry cells and return a string of the value

methods.name: _determineValidationMessage
methods.description: Returns a meaningful validation message

methods.name: _updateValidationEvent
methods.description: Fires when 'validationErrorMessage' is changed

methods.name: _submitButtonState
methods.description: Sets the button state based on if validation has been passed or not. This in turn enables or disables the Submit button.

params.name: state
params.description: Where the validation has passed or failed

methods.name: _handleIncompleteEntries
methods.description:
If required any incomplete momentObj is invalid
If not required determine if the field is blank

params.name: fieldNodes
params.description: Object of date and time cell nodes

methods.name: _loopOverCellValues
methods.description:
Checking to see if all cells are empty
If a cell has a value return false

methods.name: ready
methods.description: Sets up listeners for a variety of events fired from or passing through this component

methods.name: _focusFirstToEntry
methods.description: Focuses select on the first entry of the 'to' field

methods.name: _focusLastFromEntry
methods.description: Focuses select on the first entry of the 'from' field

methods.name: _getWrapClass
methods.description: Helper function to style the outer div

methods.name: _getFromFieldClass
methods.description: Helper function to style #fromFields

methods.name: _getToFieldClass
methods.description: Helper function to style #toFields

methods.name: _getIsValid
methods.description: Computed function to determine if everything is valid

methods.name: _isOneFieldEmpty
methods.description:
Whether exactly one field is currently empty
If only one of the two fields has been filled then treat as non valid but don't alert

methods.name: _validateRangeAndFailedClass
methods.description:
Determines if the range is valid
sets `_forcedFailedClass` on fields

methods.name: _validationMessagePriority
methods.description:
Determines which validation message to display
Show validation messages for range first, then from field, and then to field

methods.name: _handleRangeValidationMessage
methods.description: Determines whether to show a validation error message

methods.name: _dateTimeButtons
methods.description: Handle evt from a button being clicked

methods.name: _onEsc
methods.description: Handle escape key press

methods.name: _onEnter
methods.description: Handle enter key press

methods.name: _validateSetMomentObj
methods.description:
Run validation on a moment objects that have been set from the outside
This will set or unset validation errors

Run validation on the individual fields then on the range order

Useful for rangepicker to revalidate fields when interacting
with the panel

methods.name: _applyChanges
methods.description: If valid, sets the momentObjs from temp objects

methods.name: _cancelChanges
methods.description: Clear fields or reset to previous moment objs
